Global Bioabsorbable Fixation System Market Insights
Bioabsorbable Fixation System Market size was valued at USD 1.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.8 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.4% from 2024 to 2030.

Bioabsorbable Fixation System Market Overview
The global bioabsorbable fixation system market is expected to reach a valuation of USD 5.5 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.2% from 2025 to 2030. The increasing prevalence of orthopedic surgeries, sports injuries, and the rising demand for minimally invasive procedures are driving the market. These systems are used in a variety of surgical procedures, including bone fractures, ligament repair, and dental implants. The key benefits, such as reduced complications, enhanced recovery time, and lower infection risk, contribute significantly to market growth. Bioabsorbable materials are preferred over metallic implants, as they eliminate the need for removal surgeries and offer better biocompatibility. As the healthcare industry continues to advance, the adoption of bioabsorbable fixation systems is expected to rise, particularly in emerging markets.

